============================================================
8) Security Technologies and Practices
============================================================
- PBKDF2 password hashing and constant-time comparison
- Rich-text sanitization (sanitize_rich_text)
- Admin login CSRF token flow
- Input validation (email/phone/GST/URL/stock/prices)
- HttpOnly cookies used in specific flows

Where: server.py, admin/templates/login.html, admin/data/auth.json
Status: Partially hardened

Security gaps observed:
- No broad CSRF protection for all state-changing forms
- No CSP/helmet-like security headers
- Cookie hardening not uniform (Secure/SameSite not consistently set in Python runtime)
- Legacy plaintext passwords exist in data/users.json

